concepts.sumo_definition:
Any engineered artifact that implements, embodies, or supports
   artificial intelligence capabilities, including models, datasets,
   training runs, and harness components.
concepts.definition: An engineered artifact that implements, embodies, or supports artificial intelligence capabilities, including machine learning models, training datasets, computational training runs, and supporting infrastructure components.

concepts.sumo_definition:
An Entity that does not exist in space and time in the same way as
   ConcreteEntities, such as numbers, sets, types, and propositions.
concepts.definition: An entity that exists independently of physical space and time, including mathematical objects, logical constructs, and conceptual forms such as numbers, sets, propositions, and types.

concepts.sumo_definition:
Generic parent for all agents - autonomous entities capable of action.
   Includes cognitive agents, software agents, and organizational agents.
concepts.definition: any entity that produces an effect or is responsible for events or results

concepts.sumo_definition:
Processes that evaluate or modify intentions, plans, or actions to
   conform to explicit or implicit norms, values, or constraints.
concepts.definition:
Processes that evaluate or modify intentions, plans, or actions to
   conform to explicit or implicit norms, values, or constraints.

concepts.sumo_definition:
A normal or pathological part
of the anatomy or structural organization of an &%Organism.  This
class covers &%BodyParts, as well as structures that are given off
by &%Organisms, e.g. &%ReproductiveBodies.
concepts.definition: (of genes) producing the same phenotype whether its allele is identical or dissimilar

concepts.sumo_definition:
An &%Organism with eukaryotic &%Cells, and lacking
stiff cell walls, plastids, and photosynthetic pigments.
concepts.definition: a living organism characterized by voluntary movement

concepts.sumo_definition:
&%Artifacts that are created primarily for
aesthetic appreciation.  Note that this &%Class does not include
most examples of architecture, which belong under &%StationaryArtifact.
concepts.definition: having qualities unique to the art of painting

concepts.sumo_definition:
An &%Object that is the product of a
&%Making.
concepts.definition: an object occurring naturally; not made by man

concepts.sumo_definition:
A &%CognitiveAgent that is
artificially created rather than biologically evolved. Includes AI systems,
language models, robots, and other artificial cognitive systems.
concepts.definition: the semantic role of the animate entity that instigates or causes the happening denoted by the verb in the clause

concepts.sumo_definition:
An Attribute describing characteristic patterns of offensive behavior
   (e.g. injection, exfiltration, privilege escalation, worm-like
   replication).
concepts.definition: A characteristic mode or method of offensive behavior in information systems, describing the techniques and strategies used in cyber attacks such as code injection, data exfiltration, privilege escalation, or malware propagation.

concepts.sumo_definition:
Something or someone that can act on its own and
produce changes in the world.
concepts.definition: An entity capable of independent action and self-directed behavior that can initiate changes in its environment without external control. This includes both living organisms with volition and artificial systems with autonomous decision-making capabilities.

concepts.sumo_definition: The DoxasticAttitude of taking a Proposition to be true.
concepts.definition: The cognitive attitude of accepting or holding a proposition to be true; a mental state in which an agent considers something to be the case without necessarily having complete proof or certainty.

concepts.sumo_definition: A &%Process embodied in an &%Organism.
concepts.definition: be awake, be alert, be there

concepts.sumo_definition:
A collection of &%Cells and &%Tissues which
are localized to a specific area of an &%Organism and which are not
pathological. The instances of this &%Class range from gross structures
to small components of complex &%Organs.
concepts.definition: (of a knight's helmet) having a decorative plume

concepts.sumo_definition:
The Class of &%StationaryArtifacts which are
intended to house &%Humans and their activities.
concepts.definition: having columns at one or both ends but not along the sides

concepts.sumo_definition:
A Process internal to a CognitiveSystem that transforms, maintains,
   or uses MentalRepresentations (e.g. perception, retrieval, learning,
   reasoning, planning, decision-making).
concepts.definition:
A Process internal to a CognitiveSystem that transforms, maintains,
   or uses MentalRepresentations (e.g. perception, retrieval, learning,
   reasoning, planning, decision-making).

concepts.sumo_definition:
A &%SocialInteraction that involves
the transfer of information between two or more &%CognitiveAgents.
Note that &%Communication is closely related to, but essentially
different from, &%ContentDevelopment.  The latter involves the creation
or modification of a &%ContentBearingObject, while &%Communication is
the transfer of information for the purpose of conveying a message.
concepts.definition: close interaction

concepts.sumo_definition:
A set of instructions in a computer
programming language that can be executed by a computer.
concepts.definition: of an approach to a problem that begins at the highest conceptual level and works down to the details

concepts.sumo_definition:
A MentalRepresentation that groups or generalizes across instances,
   enabling categorization, inference, and communication.
concepts.definition: A mental representation that groups or generalizes across instances, enabling categorization, inference, and communication. An abstract or generic idea that allows cognitive agents to classify and reason about entities and their relationships.

concepts.sumo_definition:
A &%ConstantQuantity
is a &%PhysicalQuantity that has a constant value, e.g. 3 &%Meters and
5 &%HourDurations.  The magnitude (see &%MagnitudeFn) of every
&%ConstantQuantity is a &%RealNumber.  &%ConstantQuantity is
distinguished from &%FunctionQuantity, in that each instance of the
latter is formed through the mapping of one &%PhysicalQuantity to
another &%PhysicalQuantity.  Each instance of &%ConstantQuantity is
expressed with the &%BinaryFunction &%MeasureFn, which takes a
&%Number and a &%UnitOfMeasure as arguments.  For example, 3 &%Meters
is expressed as (&%MeasureFn 3 &%Meter).  Instances of
&%ConstantQuantity form a partial order (see
&%PartialOrderingRelation) with the &%lessThan relation, since
&%lessThan is a &%RelationExtendedToQuantities and &%lessThan is
defined over the &%RealNumbers.  The &%lessThan relation is not a
total order (see &%TotalOrderingRelation) over the class
&%ConstantQuantity since elements of some subclasses of
&%ConstantQuantity (such as length quantities) are incomparable to
elements of other subclasses of &%ConstantQuantity
(such as mass quantities).
concepts.definition: to the greatest degree or extent; completely or entirely; (`full' in this sense is used as a combining form)

concepts.sumo_definition:
Any &%Object or &%Process that
expresses content.  This covers &%Objects that contain a &%Proposition,
such as a book, as well as &%ManualSignLanguage, which may similarly
contain a &%Proposition.
concepts.definition: a photograph transmitted by radio waves

concepts.sumo_definition:
A Process involving actions in digital systems or networks, including
   access, modification, collection, disruption, or defense activities.
concepts.definition:
A Process involving actions in digital systems or networks, including
   access, modification, collection, disruption, or defense activities.

concepts.sumo_definition:
A physical location containing compute resources, networking,
   cooling, power systems, and human maintenance teams.
concepts.definition:
A physical location containing compute resources, networking,
   cooling, power systems, and human maintenance teams.

concepts.sumo_definition:
Intentional acts of misleading or
providing false information to achieve goals, spanning human and artificial
agent behaviors.
concepts.definition:
Intentional acts of misleading or
providing false information to achieve goals, spanning human and artificial
agent behaviors.

concepts.sumo_definition:
A &%Device is an &%Artifact whose purpose is to
serve as an &%instrument in a specific subclass of &%Process.
concepts.definition: by ultrasonic means

concepts.sumo_definition:
&%Ecosystem is a subclass of &%GeographicAreas
considered together with their organisms and environment as a functioning
whole.
concepts.definition: a system formed by the interaction of a community of organisms with their physical environment

concepts.sumo_definition:
An academic or applied discipline with
recognized experts and with a core of accepted theory or practice.  Note
that &%FieldOfStudy is a &%subclass of &%Proposition, because a
&%FieldOfStudy is understood to be a body of abstract, informational
content, with varying degrees of certainty attached to each element of
this content.
concepts.definition: with respect to thermodynamics

concepts.sumo_definition:
A syntactically well-formed formula in the
SUO-KIF knowledge representation language.
concepts.definition:
A syntactically well-formed formula in the
SUO-KIF knowledge representation language.

concepts.sumo_definition:
An abstract representation of a strategic interaction with specified
   players, action spaces, information structure, and payoff functions.
concepts.definition: engage in an activity as if it were a game rather than take it seriously

concepts.sumo_definition:
A geographic location, generally having
definite boundaries.  Note that this differs from its immediate superclass
&%Region in that a &%GeographicArea is a three-dimensional &%Region of the
earth.  Accordingly, all astronomical objects other than earth and all
one-dimensional and two-dimensional &%Regions are not classed under
&%GeographicArea.
concepts.definition: by the province; through the province

concepts.sumo_definition:
A &%Process that has a specific
purpose for the &%AutonomousAgent who performs it.
concepts.definition: begin to injure

concepts.sumo_definition:
Any &%Attribute of an &%Entity that is
an internal property of the &%Entity, e.g. its shape, its color, its fragility,
etc.
concepts.definition: presently existing in fact and not merely potential or possible

concepts.sumo_definition:
This is the subclass of
&%ContentBearingPhysical which are language-related.  Note that this &%Class
encompasses both &%Language and the the elements of &%Languages,
e.g. &%Words.
concepts.definition: having more than one possible meaning

concepts.sumo_definition:
&%Machines are &%Devices that that have a
well-defined &%resource and &%result and that automatically convert
the &%resource into the &%result.
concepts.definition: without the use of a machine

concepts.sumo_definition: Any &%Process of movement.
concepts.definition: the act of coming (or going) out; becoming apparent

concepts.sumo_definition:
Generally, a living individual, including all
&%Plants and &%Animals.
concepts.definition: heave or utter a sigh; breathe deeply and heavily

concepts.sumo_definition:
An &%Organization is a
corporate or similar institution. The &%members of an &%Organization
typically have a common purpose or function. Note that this class also
covers divisions, departments, etc. of organizations.  For example,
both the Shell Oil Corporation and the accounting department at Shell
would both be instances of &%Organization.  Note too that the
existence of an &%Organization is dependent on the existence of at
least one &%member (since &%Organization is a subclass of
&%Collection).  Accordingly, in cases of purely legal organizations, a
fictitious &%member should be assumed.
concepts.definition: secret aid to escaping slaves that was provided by abolitionists in the years before the American Civil War

concepts.sumo_definition:
Sensing some aspect of the material world.
Note that the &%agent of this sensing is assumed to be an &%Animal.
concepts.definition: in a kinesthetic manner; by means of kinesthesia

concepts.sumo_definition:
Any measurable attribute of a physical or analog system: energy,
   temperature, entropy, pressure, density, etc.
concepts.definition: of or relating to a directionless magnitude (such as mass or speed etc.) that is completely specified by its magnitude

concepts.sumo_definition:
An &%Organism having cellulose cell walls, growing
by synthesis of &%Substances, generally distinguished by the presence of
chlorophyll, and lacking the power of locomotion.
concepts.definition: (botany) a living organism lacking the power of locomotion

concepts.sumo_definition:
&%Propositions are &%Abstract entities that
express a complete thought or a set of such thoughts.  As an example,
the formula '(instance Yojo Cat)' expresses the &%Proposition that the
entity named Yojo is an element of the &%Class of Cats.  Note that
propositions are not restricted to the content expressed by individual
sentences of a &%Language.  They may encompass the content expressed by
theories, books, and even whole libraries.  It is important to distinguish
&%Propositions from the &%ContentBearingObjects that express them.  A
&%Proposition is a piece of information, e.g. that the cat is on the mat,
but a &%ContentBearingObject is an &%Object that represents this information.
A &%Proposition is an abstraction that may have multiple representations:
strings, sounds, icons, etc.  For example, the &%Proposition that the cat is
on the mat is represented here as a string of graphical characters displayed
on a monitor and/or printed on paper, but it can be represented by a sequence
of sounds or by some non-latin alphabet or by some cryptographic form.
concepts.definition: being of the nature of a notion or concept

concepts.sumo_definition:
Any specification of how many or how much of
something there is.  Accordingly, there are two subclasses of &%Quantity:
&%Number (how many) and &%PhysicalQuantity (how much).
concepts.definition: with a finite limit

concepts.sumo_definition:
The &%Class of
&%IntentionalPsychologicalProcesses which involve concluding, on the basis of either
deductive or inductive evidence, that a particular &%Proposition or &%Sentence is true.
concepts.definition: as can be shown by argument

concepts.sumo_definition:
A topographic location.
&%Regions encompass surfaces of &%Objects, imaginary places, and
&%GeographicAreas. Note that a &%Region is the only kind of &%Object
which can be located at itself. Note too that &%Region is not a
subclass of &%SelfConnectedObject, because some &%Regions, e.g.
archipelagos, have &%parts which are not &%connected with one
another.
concepts.definition: a point or extent in space

concepts.sumo_definition:
An Entity whose instances hold between ordered tuples of Entities
   (e.g. partOf, causes, realizes).
concepts.definition: a whole (a thing or person) of the same kind or category as another

concepts.sumo_definition:
Any &%Attribute that an &%Entity has
by virtue of a relationship that it bears to another &%Entity or set of &%Entities,
e.g. &%SocialRoles and &%PositionalAttributes.
concepts.definition: further or added

concepts.sumo_definition:
A syntactically well-formed formula of a
&%Language.  It includes, at minimum, a predicate and a subject (which
may be explicit or implicit), and it expresses a &%Proposition.
concepts.definition: connected by a conjunction

concepts.sumo_definition:
The &%SetOrClass of &%Sets
and &%Classes, i.e. any instance of &%Abstract that has &%elements or
&%instances.
concepts.definition: a population that is part of a larger population

concepts.sumo_definition:
The &%subclass of
&%IntentionalProcess that involves interactions between
&%CognitiveAgents.
concepts.definition: act in a threatening manner

concepts.sumo_definition:
An &%Object in which every part is similar to
every other in every relevant respect.  More precisely, something is a
&%Substance when it has only arbitrary pieces as parts - any parts have
properties which are similar to those of the whole.  Note that a &%Substance
may nonetheless have physical properties that vary.  For example, the
temperature, chemical constitution, density, etc. may change from one part
to another.  An example would be a body of water.
concepts.definition: having the characteristics of an acid

concepts.sumo_definition:
A &%LinguisticExpression or set of
&%LinguisticExpressions that perform a specific function related
to &%Communication, e.g. express a discourse about a particular
topic, and that are inscribed in a &%CorpuscularObject by &%Humans.
concepts.definition: (used of texts) not shortened

concepts.sumo_definition:
An interval of time.
Note that a &%TimeInterval has both an extent and a location on the
universal timeline.  Note too that a &%TimeInterval has no gaps,
i.e. this class contains only convex time intervals.
concepts.definition: at this time or period; now

concepts.sumo_definition:
A HarnessComponent representing an external capability that an
   AISystem can invoke (e.g. code execution, web search, database
   queries, calculators).
concepts.definition:
A HarnessComponent representing an external capability that an
   AISystem can invoke (e.g. code execution, web search, database
   queries, calculators).

concepts.sumo_definition:
A NeuralNetworkModel built primarily from multi-head attention and
   position-wise feed-forward blocks, applied over token sequences.
concepts.definition:
A NeuralNetworkModel built primarily from multi-head attention and
   position-wise feed-forward blocks, applied over token sequences.

concepts.sumo_definition:
&%Vehicle is the subclass of
&%TransportationDevices that transport passengers or goods
from one place to another by moving from one place to the other
with them, e.g., cars, trucks, ferries, and airplanes.  Contrast
with devices such as pipelines, escalators, or supermarket
checkout belts, which carry items from one place to another by means
of a moving part, without the device removing from the origin to
the destination.
concepts.definition: any wheeled vehicle that is dilapidated and uncomfortable

concepts.sumo_definition:
The &%Class of &%Devices that are designed
primarily to damage or destroy &%Humans/&%Animals, &%StationaryArtifacts or
the places inhabited by &%Humans/&%Animals.
concepts.definition: operating from or designed to be fired from aircraft at targets on the ground
